body_html:
@aaroey Thanks for your reply.

I tried tensorflow-native, FP32 and FP16. All three models seem to have the same inference speed.

The error nvinfer1::DimsCHW nvinfer1::getCHW(const nvinfer1::Dims&): Assertion 'd.nbDims >= 3' failed is caused by a known bug in the TRT 4.0 library, and TRT 5.0 should fix the problem. Last time when I tried to use TRT 5.0 with TF1.11, but it complains that TF is built with TRT 4.0 and does NOT support TRT 5.0. I haven't tried your tf-nightly-gpu yet. Does it support TRT 5.0?

Thanks!

@aaroey Thanks for your reply.

I tried tensorflow-native, FP32 and FP16. All three models seem to have the same inference speed.

`The error nvinfer1::DimsCHW nvinfer1::getCHW(const nvinfer1::Dims&): Assertion 'd.nbDims >= 3' failed is caused by a known bug in the TRT 4.0 library, and TRT 5.0 should fix the problem.` Last time when I tried to use TRT 5.0 with TF1.11, but it complains that TF is built with TRT 4.0 and does NOT support TRT 5.0. I haven't tried your `tf-nightly-gpu` yet. Does it support TRT 5.0?

Thanks!
